Package cp213

Class SingleList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

java.lang.Object
cp213.SingleLink<T>
cp213.SingleList<T>
Type Parameters:
T - this SingleList data type.
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>
public class SingleList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends SingleLink<T>
A simple linked list structure of Node T objects. Only the T data contained in the stack is visible through the standard list methods. Extends the SingleLink class, which already defines the head node, length, iterator, and toArray.
Version:
2020-10-16
Author:
David Brown

    • clean

      public void clean()
      Removes duplicates from this SingleList. The list contains one and only one of each value formerly present in this SingleList. The first occurrence of each value is preserved.

    • combine

      public void combine​(SingleList<T> left, SingleList<T> right)
      Combines contents of two lists into a third. Values are alternated from the origin lists into this SingleList. The origin lists are empty when finished. NOTE: data must not be moved, only nodes.
      Parameters:
      left - The first list to combine with this SingleList.
      right - The second list to combine with this SingleList.

    • split

      public void split​(SingleList<T> left, SingleList<T> right)
      Splits the contents of this SingleList into the left and right SingleLists. Moves nodes only - does not move data or call the high-level methods insert or remove. this SingleList is empty when done. The first half of this SingleList is moved to left, and the last half of this SingleList is moved to right. If the resulting lengths are not the same, left should have one more item than right.
      Parameters:
      left - The first SingleList to move nodes to.
      right - The second SingleList to move nodes to.

    • splitAlternate

      public void splitAlternate​(SingleList<T> left, SingleList<T> right)
      Splits the contents of this SingleList into the left and right SingleLists. Moves nodes only - does not move data or call the high-level methods insert or remove. this SingleList is empty when done. Nodes are moved alternately from this SingleList to left and right.
      Parameters:
      left - The first SingleList to move nodes to.
      right - The second SingleList to move nodes to.

    • union

      public void union​(SingleList<T> left, SingleList<T> right)
      Creates a union of two other SingleLists into this SingleList. Copies data to this list. left and right SingleLists are unchanged.
      Parameters:
      left - The first SingleList to create a union from.
      right - The second SingleList to create a union from.
